touching his portfolio _ just by moving to Arizona or New Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   Savings like those point up the limitations of the familiar rule
of thumb that says in retirement you need 70 to 80 percent of your
pre-retirement income. &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (325-WORD OPTIONAL TRIM BEGINS HERE) &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Which is not to knock the rule, as it's based on some pretty
