 World rights except Great Britain and Australia. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Color slides and black and white photos of Paul Hogan and Linda
Kozlowski are available. &QL; 
 &UR; By IVOR DAVIS &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Paul Hogan is back in an offbeat new movie that takes him far
from his swashbuckling persona, Crocadile Dundee.
</P>
<P>
   ``Floating Away,'' (airing Aug. 30 on Showtime) is a picaresque
comedy drama with Rosanna Arquette as a boozy mother trying to
regain custody of her baby. Along the way she meets Shane (Hogan),
a womanizing, reformed alcoholic, and a paraplegic.
</P>
<P>
   (To publish this ``separate buy'' column it must be purchased --
the rate is not prohibitive -- from one of these New York Times
Syndicate sales representatives:
</P>
<P>
   (--Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942.
