terrorist training camp is like shooting a .45 at a swarm of bees.
You may kill a few bees, but the rest are going to get mad.
Terrorists are not good at learning from messages and tend to
respond with car bombs. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   LYNCH-COLUMN (Albany, N.Y.) _ In case you haven't noticed, we
live in a world where we're increasingly on our own in solving all
but the most monumental of problems. Take what happened to Debbie
Zotto, for example: One day last week she encountered a skunk. By
DAN LYNCH.
</P>
