   &UR; OTHER INTERNATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-FLOODS (Beijing) _ As the flooding crests in some parts of
the country, the hard work of trying to contain the spread of
epidemics and disease begins. By Elisabeth Rosenthal.
</P>
<P>
   NIRELAND-U.S. (Dublin) _ The U.S. had denied a travel visa to a
prominent Irish Republican leader believed to have contacts with
terrorists who killed 28 people in a car bomb attack in Omagh,
Northern Ireland on Saturday. By James F. Clarity.
</P>
