<HEADER>
A6294 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN-     08-21 0699
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN-2ndTake-TEX </SLUG>
 
UNDATED: there's more. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   One of my favorite features is the ``rainsense''
windshield-wiper system, which automatically detect when water is
hitting the windshield and turns the wipers on.
</P>
<P>
   The ``Magnasteer'' power-steering system adjusts to the speed of
the car. If the car is at highway speeds, the power assist is much
less than it would be during low-speed maneuvering, such as
parallel parking. Tighter, stiffer steering at highway speeds makes
for surer control.
</P>
<P>
   A computerized driver-information center can be set to display
its information in five languages: English, French, Spanish,
Japanese or German. This reflects Cadillac's efforts to market the
Seville worldwide as a competitor to such Japanese luxury cars as
the Lexus and Infiniti, and European bluebloods such at
Mercedes-Benz, Jaguar, BMW and Audi.
</P>
<P>
   Audiophiles will appreciate the Bose 4.0
AM/FM/cassette/compact-disc system, which is among the best you'll
find anywhere. The average Seville buyer, however, will probably
never crank up the volume enough to appreciate just how good this
stereo is. The system has 425 watts of eardrum-blowing power and
eight speakers, enough to produce the same volume you would hear on
the front row of your average Rolling Stones concert, although
without distortion.
</P>
<P>
   The optional On Star system, satellite- and cellular-phone-based
navigation and emergency communications, tracks the car through the
Global Positioning System satellites and notifies the On Star
operator automatically if either a front or side air bag deploys in
the Seville. The exact location of the car is transmitted to the
center, where operators call the appropriate emergency services.
The operator is immediately available in non-emergency situations
to guide you to your destination, send you to the nearest
automatic-teller machine, or help you with hotel reservations,
among other things. The system pinpoints your current location on
the operator's electronic map to within 200 feet and identifies
you.
</P>
<P>
   With all this high-tech stuff, let's not forget what's under the
hood in the STS. This car comes with Cadillac's outstanding
Northstar system: a 4.6-liter, 32-valve, V-8 engine rated at 300
horsepower and 295 foot-pounds of torque, coupled with that
smooth-shifting, four-speed automatic transmission. Unlike the
Lexus LS 400 and most of its European competitors, the Seville has
front-wheel drive, which is better than rear-wheel drive on
slippery surfaces.
</P>
<P>
   There is power galore at your disposal, plenty enough for
high-speed cruising, lane-changing, hill-climbing, or freeway
merging. The Seville will even pull a trailer of up to 3,000
pounds.
</P>
<P>
   Other standard amenities include power mirrors/windows/door
locks/headlights, dual-zone automatic climate control (with
separate controls for driver and front passenger), electronic
traction control, cruise control, and power tilt and telescopic
steering column.
</P>
<P>
   Leather seats are standard, of course. Our test car came with a
$495 wood-trim package for the steering wheel and shift knob. The
only other option was Z-rated tires (made for speeds in excess of
100 mph), a $250 addition. Total cost of the vehicle was $49,607,
including $665 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   My only real gripe was with the rear seat. The three inches
trimmed off the length of the Seville apparently came at the
expense of rear-seat leg room, making it a tight fit for most
adults. It's not all that easy to get into and out of the back
seat, either.
</P>
<P>
   Fuel economy is surprisingly good for such a capable performer.
EPA estimates are 17 miles per gallon in the city and 26 mpg on the
highway. The fuel tank holds 18.5 gallons of gasoline.
</P>
<P>
   (G. Chambers Williams III writes on transportation issues for
the Fort Worth Star-Telegram. His mailing address is
Star-Telegram/Northeast, 3201 Airport Freeway, Suite 108, Bedford,
Texas 76021; his E-mail address is chambers(at)star-telegram.com.
Fax: (817) 685-3883. Check out his Wheelin' new-car review column
weekly on the Internet at
ww.netarrant.net/today/news/opinions/necol.htm. Visit the
Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
