<P>
   BBN-DODGERS _ From consistency to chaos. That's the story for
the Dodgers since the Fox takeover. Once a model of consistency,
the Los Angeles franchise is reeling from strange change.
(Rosenberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AJC BRAVES FARM TEAM SERIES _ Day 7
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MINORS-GREENVILLE _ GREENVILLE, S.C. _ George Lombard was
happy when Aug. 1 arrived. After weeks of hearing he might be
traded by the Braves for needed bullpen help, Lombard knows he
still has a chance to reach the majors in his hometown. After
turning down a football scholarship at Georgia to sign with
Atlanta, the private school graduate struggled for his first four
seasons. But now he is showing the talent that the Braves always
thought he would. (Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8
p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MINORS-GREENVILLE-CHAPEL _ Baseball Chapel offers spiritual
support to players struggling in the minors. In Greenville, the
weekly services are led by former major leaguers Marty Clary and
Jose Alvarez. (Curtright, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m.
ET.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MINORS-GREENVILLE-FACTS _ Greenville fact box. (Curtright,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-WNBA _ The future seems bright for the WNBA and the Houston
Comets, which concluded their second regular season last night. The
league generated a reported average attendance of more than 10,000
fans per game this season, something the NBA needed 29 years to
achieve. Scoring in the league is up, turnovers are down and the
game is popular enoughthat the team with the worst record, the
Washington Mystics, has the league's best attendance. Then there's
the Comets, whose winning percentage rates with any team sport
ever. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-COWBOYS -Advance of the Cowboys' game at St. Louis against
the St. Louis Rams, the most important preseason game of the fall.
The starters will get extensive playing time. They need it. (Cantu,
Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-FSU-PREVIEW _ The Road to College Football previews Florida
State, which is expected to contend for the national championship
this season. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m.
ET.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FBC-FSU-BOX _ Florida State fact box. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR PAGE _ An open page on this weekend's NASCAR race in
Bristol, Tenn. WITH LAYOUT. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Will be
posted by 4 p.m. EDT on Friday, Aug. 21.
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR _ Jeff Gordon eyes fifth consecutive victory and shot at
modern-era NASCAR history. (McCollister, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR-NOTES _ NASCAR notebook. (McCollister, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Eds: The AJC's weekly racing page is being on posted on Friday
for Saturday papers because this weekend's race in Bristol, Tenn.,
is on Saturday instead of Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   GYM-CHAMPIONSHIPS _ Coverage of U.S. Gymnastics Championships.
(Rosen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   STADIUM _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Construction bids for the proposed
baseball stadium in downtown Dayton came in high, forcing project
planners to consider more cost cutting and another round of bids.
Companies that have bid on the job said the stadium needs to be
shrunk or the $16 million estimated cost needs to go up.
(Bebbington, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MCCOY-COLUMN _ PITTSBURGH _ Jack McKeon thumbed through a
statistical sheet before a recent game in Three Rivers Stadium and
his finger stopped on the line with the numbers for pitcher Dennis
Reyes. ``I'd like to see Reyes have a good September to vault him
into next year, give him a little confidence boost going into
spring training next year,'' the Cincinnati Reds manager said.
September? How about August? On a recent night, the 21-year-old
Reyes cranked up his fourth straight excellent August start for the
Reds. (McCoy, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
