Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-WNBA _ The future seems bright for the WNBA and the Houston
Comets, which concluded their second regular season last night. The
league generated a reported average attendance of more than 10,000
fans per game this season, something the NBA needed 29 years to
achieve. Scoring in the league is up, turnovers are down and the
game is popular enoughthat the team with the worst record, the
Washington Mystics, has the league's best attendance. Then there's
the Comets, whose winning percentage rates with any team sport
ever. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-COWBOYS -Advance of the Cowboys' game at St. Louis against
the St. Louis Rams, the most important preseason game of the fall.
The starters will get extensive playing time. They need it. (Cantu,
Austin American-Statesman) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
