   JAPAN-BANK (Tokyo) _ Long Term Credit Bank of Japan, the
troubled institution that has become an unfortunate symbol of the
problems of Japan's banking system and the government's inability
to act swiftly to fix them, announces a restructuring that will
pave the way for an injection of public money and an eventual
merger with Sumitomo Trust. The restructuring signaled that the
government is hoping to steer the battered Japanese financial
system to a ``soft'' landing, rather than the swift, relentless
overhaul many foreign investors long for. By Stephanie Strom.
