</P>
<P>
   INVEST-FRAUD (New York) _ Federal law enforcement officials say
that the leaders of the Association of Individual Ministries,
including its head, Charles R. Groeschel, are architects of one of
the more exploitive frauds in recent memory, one that snared about
2,000 victims nationwide between 1996 and earlier this year. In
what appears to be an unusual mix of cyberspace and religious
hucksterism, Groeschel used the association as the centerpiece of a
scheme that promised copious _ and ultimately nonexistent _
financial returns, according to the U.S. attorney's office in
Manhattan, which has filed criminal charges against Groeschel. By
Timothy L. O'Brien.
