   TV-PERKINS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ First, the title. Producers Bonnie and Terry Turner
tossed around dozens of names for their '70s-based sitcom,
beginning Sunday night on Fox, and nothing stuck. Not ``Reelin' in
the Years,'' not ``Feelin' Alright,'' not ``The Kids Are All
Right.'' Frustrated and a little fried, the producing partners took
the name that was right under their noses. Test audiences could
never remember the show's title and would finally mutter in
frustration, ``You know, that '70s show.'' By KEN PARISH PERKINS.
Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
