   UNDATED _ A stranger is traveling through town late one night
when his car crashes in a drenching rain. After a long string of
motorists passes him by and he is near death, he pens a note saying
he would rather die than live in a world so void of compassion. I
read this story, or rather some version of it, nearly 20 years ago
while a student at the University of Southern Mississippi. The
particulars, of course, have faded with the passage of time. But
I've never forgotten the utter horror in it, or its message about
the human condition. By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES. Story has moved in
