<P>
   UNDATED _ The Gallup pollsters and their media partners, CNN and
USA Today, have been busy explaining a discrepancy in their instant
analysis of public reaction to President Clinton's post-grand-jury
speech Monday night. Gallup's initial polling after the speech
suggested that the percentage of respondents holding a favorable
view of Clinton had plummeted from 60 percent to 40 percent. The
precipitous drop was amazing, especially when compared with
Clinton's 62 percent job approval rating in the same poll. By BILL
THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
