   LABBE-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ I'll admit to being way behind the curve on this
tidbit of information, but then, I haven't had to renew my driver's
license in person in more than six year. The white sign with its
bold red letters, hanging above the heads of the Texas Department
of Public Safety employees, announced in no uncertain terms that
all applicants must present a Social Security card to receive a
new, renewed or replacement driver's license. For something that
was never supposed to be used as universal identification, my
nine-digit Social Security number sure gets a workout. By J.R.
LABBE. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
