DRUGS-AZ (Undated) - Arizona teens are using illegal drugs,
especially marijuana, at a dramatically higher rate than teens
nationwide, a federal study says. More than 13 percent of Arizona
youths aged 12 to 17 reported smoking marijuana recently. The
national number: 9.6 percent and in California, 6.6 percent.
Overall, 16.8 percent of Arizona youths 12-17 reported using
illicit drugs of any kind. National number: 11.7 percent. With
DRUGS-COMPARE. By JEFF BARKER. Story will move in the ``A``
category.  &QL; 
