   w/
</P>
<P>
   STRIKE-RESPONSE (Undated) -- The American missile attacks follow
the Israeli model of a quick, tough response to terrorism _ a shift
in US strategy being praised for finally putting militants on
notice that they'll pay a high price if they continue their
aggression. By Adam Pertman.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   STRIKE-ANALYSIS (Undated) -- It was a week that showed President
Clinton's weaknesses. No matter what he does, his motives are under
suspicion. By David M. Shribman. 1050 words. (i and w coding)
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   STRIKE-POLICY (Washington) -- President Clinton was quick to
strike, but there are plenty of other hotspots the administration
