<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-LEATHER (Undated) _ Americans had flings with vinyl,
synthetics and crushed velour. Now, snuggling into their cars and
trucks, they seem to have developed a leather fetish. Auto makers
tripled their use of leather from 1982 to 1992, according to a
trade group, Leather Industries of America. By Dan Neil. (Moved).
Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-SMART-EXOTIC-HIDES (Undated) _ While cowhide is now seen as
a luxury, in the early days of the automobile it was the only
choice for seating surfaces. In the grand automotive era of the
late 20s and 30s, custom coach builders availed themselves of a
menagerie of hides, from anteater to zebra, to distinguish their
artworks from the hoi polloi. By Dan Neil. (Moved). Photo.
</P>
