orchestras, but Mrs. Horowitz, who died Friday at her Manhattan
home at the age of 90, played a unique part in this century's music
world. For almost all of her life she was at the center of a world
that lionized her father, Arturo Toscanini, and adored her husband,
Vladimir Horowitz. (Sam Falk/New York Times Photo)
