<P>
   (NYT19) NEW YORK -- Aug. 21, 1998 -- OBIT-HOROWITZ-B&AMP;W, 8-21 --
Vladimir and Wanda Horowitz at their home on Fifth Avenue in 1965.
She wrote no symphonies, played on no concert stages, conducted no
orchestras, but Mrs. Horowitz, who died Friday at her Manhattan
home at the age of 90, played a unique part in this century's music
world. For almost all of her life she was at the center of a world
that lionized her father, Arturo Toscanini, and adored her husband,
Vladimir Horowitz. (Sam Falk/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) NEW YORK -- Aug. 21, 1998 -- INVEST-FRAUD, 8-21 --
Former members of the Association of Individual Ministries, or AIM,
who say they lost money. From left to right: William Corbin, Nola
Pendergrass, Andrew Williams, The Rev. George Samuels and Richard
Clark. Federal law-enforcement officials say that the leaders of
AIM, including its head, Charles Groeschel, are architects of an
exploitive fraud that has snared about 2,000 victims nationwide
since 1996. (Ruby Washington/New York Times Photo) *LITE
